```julia
function timezone_bumper(dt::DateTime, bump::Integer=3)
    if !isdate(dt) && !isnan(bump)
        return DateTime(dt.year, dt.month, dt.day, dt.hour + bump, dt.minute, dt.second, dt.millisecond, tz=dt.timezone)
    else
        error("Cannot apply time zone bump to a Date or NaN value.")
    end
end
```

This function checks if `dt` is a DateTime and not NaN. If so, it increments the hour by `bump` hours and returns the new DateTime with the same timezone as the original. If `dt` is not a DateTime or `bump` is NaN, an error is thrown.
